  "text": "During pregnancy, the development of sigmoid volvulus can occur as result of a redundant or abnormally mobile sigmoid colon, displaced and led to twist around its point of fixation by the enlargement of the uterus; the fact that most reported cases occurred during third trimester of pregnancy corroborates this hypothesis [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] .",
